Pistacia lentiscus

   [8690.jpg]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Sapindales:Anacardiaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names mastic tree, lentisk, mastich, pistachio, lentisque,
   mastikboom, lentisco, mastixbaum, mastixstrauch, lentisco verdadeiro,
   almacegueira, daro, daroeira, aroeira da praia, mastiktræ
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 8690

   Notes
   Ecology
   It has a good capacity to resprout after cutting or fire.
   Habitat: It is frequently found among the scrubby
   growth of shores e.g. together with carob trees and
   palmetto. It is rarely seen growing inland where it can be
   found in woods together with holm oaks. In mountains or in
   hilly lands of warm Mediterranean areas the cover by the
   plant may be more or less total and uniform, particularly
   in areas with a desertification risk.
   Environment
   Altitude:
   Temperature: Mature plant can withstand winter
   temperatures down to -9°C. Reported temperature range for
   growth is 12-40°C with the optimum between 18-24°C.
   Water: It is drought resistant. Reported annual
   rainfall range for growth is 200-2000 mm with the optimum
   between 400-800 mm.
   Radiation
   Range & intensity: It thrives in full sunlight and
   it does not like cold shady places.
   Photoperiodism:
   Soil:
   Physical: Often found on sandy soil, dry rocky
   slopes and sandy loams. Soils should be dry to moist.
   Chemical: Reported soil pH range for growth is 6-8.5
   with the optimum between 6.5-8.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
